            "answer_text": "If the subject is singular, the verb used is also singular. For instance, The baker bakes a cake. If the subject is plural, the verb used is also plural. For instance, The bakers bake a cake. Hence, the sentence \u2018Two and two makes four.\u2019 is a grammatically incorrect sentence as the singular verb \u2018makes\u2019 does not agree with the plural compound subject \u2018two and two.\u2019 The sentence \u2018Two and two make four\u2019 is a grammatically correct sentence as the plural verb \u2018make\u2019 agrees with the plural compound subject \u2018two and two\u2019.  Nikhil Lunia ",
